Ecology and distribution.
Most likely an amphibiont. The species united under the synonym
A. maitai
(see Remarks and
Gagarin & Gusakov 2013d
), have been reported previously only from soil in New Zealand and India , plus in one river in Republic of South Africa (
Yeates 1967
;
Baqri & Jairajpuri 1968
;
Botha & Heyns 1991
). In Vietnam , this nematode was found in water bodies of various types , but exclusively in shallow water biotopes.
